sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1789023
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a device which contains the sequence of TALE based IAAM, TALE based IAAH and scaffold 3. Through this device, we can test and verify that our scaffold can strengthen the function of IAA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chushu Zhu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: We obtained it through the contribution of our basic subparts.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This is the experimental group of our project. Our theory is feasible if the functional parameter of this group is stronger than the group of negative control.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1789012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a promoter. It has a strong RBS restriction site following it which can guarantee the high efficiency of our project.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jiaqi Sun
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It is formed by our basic parts.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We want to construct a promoter which has RBS30 itself for RBS30 is small. If we supply a promoter with RBS, the efficiency of building will be high.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1789001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the coding sequence of the enzyme Indoleacetimide hydrolase Iaa H. This enzyme catalyses the hydrolysis of indoleacetamide to indoleacetate and ammonia. This part is gathered from the 2-step pathway in Pseudomonas savastanoi producing the auxin, indole-3-acetic acid.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xinyuan Qiu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is gained from the part BBa_K515100 by PCR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: In order to get the whole sequence of IAAH, we removed the RBS and other irrelevant sequences in K515100 when designing the PCR primers.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1789009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a engineered TAL effector that can bind with the DNA sequence 5'-GATAAACACCTTTC-3'
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xinyuan Qiu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is built and standardized by ourselves using GATEWAY technique.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The part sequence should be able to correctly and efficiently bind with corresponding DNA, so we used bioinformatics tools to help us designing this sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1789002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is another copy of the RBS30 (BBa_B0030). It is a Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xinyuan Qiu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The part sequence was gained from the registry, the part is annealed from the ssDNA synthesized by Life(R).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The reason why we built this part by ourselves is that the copy of B0030 in the 2015 DNA distribution we received is sequenced as incorrect. And same problem also occurred in several other teams.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1789000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the coding sequence of tryptophan-2-mono-oxygenase. This enzyme catalyzes the oxidative carboxylation of L-tryptophan to indole-3-acetamide which acts as an intermediate to the production of indole-3-acetic acid in the IAM pathway.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xinyuan Qiu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is gained from BBa_K515100 by PCR. The IAA producing pathway originates from Pseudomonas savastanoi.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The reason why er designed this part is that we needed IAA producing pathway as a reporter in our system, and the IAAM and IAAH CDS needed to be fused with the coding sequence of the TAL effector we engineered. So we used the part BBa_K515100, which contains the CDS of IaaM and IaaH, and used PCR to eliminate the RBS sequence from the 5' region of the CDS.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1789008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a engineered TAL effector that can bind with the DNA sequence 5'-GGAGGCACCGGTGG-3'
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xinyuan Qiu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is built by NJU_CHINA using GATEWAY technique. We standardized this part by ourselves.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The part sequence should be able to correctly and efficiently bind with corresponding DNA, so we used bioinformatics tools to help us designing this sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LacI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Inverting regulatory region controlled by LacI (BBa_C0010, BBa_C0011, etc.)

The pLac regulatory region is a 243 base-pair sequence with standard BioBrick prefix and suffix sections on its ends. It contains two protein binding sites: CAP, which is generally present in E.coli and is assocciated with cell health and availability of glucose., and LacI, the Lac inhibitor BBa_C0010 which binds in an dimerized cooperative manner to inhibit the transcription of the protein that follows. In the presence of lactose or IPTG, an analog of lactose, LacI is unable to correctly bind and inhibit transcription. This allows BBa_R0010 to be used as a inverter or as a detector of lactose or IPTG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The Plac insert was PCR'd from the MG1655 strain of E.coli K12.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: LacI binds to this regulator. This part is incompatible with species containing active LacI coding regions. Lactose and IPTG disable the operation of LacI and this regulator. This part is incompatible with environments containing lactose or lactose analogs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
